column1: The training data consisted of 102 instances
While the test data consisted of 52 instances.
A one to one multi-class approach was used for the data
Each model is created using only two classes from the entire class list
These models then vote on the final class
Above is the matrix containing the final class predictions
The leftmost column contains the original class of each instance of the test data
The rightmost column contains the final prediction of the algorithm
Each of the columns in between corresponds to the output from one model.
The average prediction accuracy over ten executions was: 0.8557692307692306
